version_description: This version uses very simple chords and offers a way of playing the song with a capo.

The chorus of this song can be played with the same chords of the intro (F#min instead of A69 and D instead of Dsus2), this version change just for this two chords that Steven Wilson played live with Ninet Tayeb in the Facebook page "Deutschlandfunk Kultur" during the chorus.
Adapted guitar part from a keyboard centered song. Very simple song revolving around 3 musical ideas featuring some interesting chord choices.

This song is kinda weird to play acoustic because it's pretty much based on one chord for the entire song, so if you guys have any ideas to make this more "playable" feel free to edit the tab or whatever you prefer.
This version of the tab is much simpler than other versions and does not require a capo.
Found the chords of this song, so you can play it acustic. it's in E standard tuning, 115 bpm, no capo needed.
